40static void
41nv50_disp_mthd_list(struct nv50_disp *disp, int debug, u32 base, int c,
42 const struct nv50_disp_mthd_list *list, int inst)
43{
44 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &disp->base.engine.subdev;
45 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
46 int i;
47
48 for (i = 0; list->data[i].mthd; i++) {
49 if (list->data[i].addr) {
50 u32 next = nvkm_rd32(device, list->data[i].addr + base + 0);
51 u32 prev = nvkm_rd32(device, list->data[i].addr + base + c);
52 u32 mthd = list->data[i].mthd + (list->mthd * inst);
53 const char *name = list->data[i].name;
54 char mods[16];
55
56 if (prev != next)
57 snprintf(mods, sizeof(mods), "-> %08x", next);
58 else
59 snprintf(mods, sizeof(mods), "%13c", ' ');
60
61 nvkm_printk_(subdev, debug, info,
62 "\t%04x: %08x %s%s%s\n",
63 mthd, prev, mods, name ? " // " : "",
64 name ? name : "");
65 }
66 }
67}
68
69void
70nv50_disp_chan_mthd(struct nv50_disp_chan *chan, int debug)
71{
72 struct nv50_disp *disp = chan->root->disp;
73 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &disp->base.engine.subdev;
74 const struct nv50_disp_chan_mthd *mthd = chan->mthd;
75 const struct nv50_disp_mthd_list *list;
76 int i, j;
77
78 if (debug > subdev->debug)
79 return;
80
81 for (i = 0; (list = mthd->data[i].mthd) != NULL; i++) {
82 u32 base = chan->head * mthd->addr;
83 for (j = 0; j < mthd->data[i].nr; j++, base += list->addr) {
84 const char *cname = mthd->name;
85 const char *sname = "";
86 char cname_[16], sname_[16];
87
88 if (mthd->addr) {
89 snprintf(cname_, sizeof(cname_), "%s %d",
90 mthd->name, chan->chid);
91 cname = cname_;
92 }
93
94 if (mthd->data[i].nr > 1) {
95 snprintf(sname_, sizeof(sname_), " - %s %d",
96 mthd->data[i].name, j);
97 sname = sname_;
98 }
99
100 nvkm_printk_(subdev, debug, info, "%s%s:\n", cname, sname);
101 nv50_disp_mthd_list(disp, debug, base, mthd->prev,
102 list, j);
103 }
104 }
105}
106
107static void
108nv50_disp_chan_uevent_fini(struct nvkm_event *event, int type, int index)
109{
110 struct nv50_disp *disp = container_of(event, typeof(*disp), uevent);
111 struct nvkm_device *device = disp->base.engine.subdev.device;
112 nvkm_mask(device, 0x610028, 0x00000001 << index, 0x00000000 << index);
113 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x610020, 0x00000001 << index);
114}
115
116static void
117nv50_disp_chan_uevent_init(struct nvkm_event *event, int types, int index)
118{
119 struct nv50_disp *disp = container_of(event, typeof(*disp), uevent);
120 struct nvkm_device *device = disp->base.engine.subdev.device;
121 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x610020, 0x00000001 << index);
122 nvkm_mask(device, 0x610028, 0x00000001 << index, 0x00000001 << index);
123}
124
125void
126nv50_disp_chan_uevent_send(struct nv50_disp *disp, int chid)
127{
128 struct nvif_notify_uevent_rep {
129 } rep;
130
131 nvkm_event_send(&disp->uevent, 1, chid, &rep, sizeof(rep));
132}
133
134int
135nv50_disp_chan_uevent_ctor(struct nvkm_object *object, void *data, u32 size,
136 struct nvkm_notify *notify)
137{
138 struct nv50_disp_chan *chan = nv50_disp_chan(object);
139 union {
140 struct nvif_notify_uevent_req none;
141 } *args = data;
142 int ret;
143
144 if (nvif_unvers(args->none)) {
145 notify->size = sizeof(struct nvif_notify_uevent_rep);
146 notify->types = 1;
147 notify->index = chan->chid;
148 return 0;
149 }
150
151 return ret;
152}
153
154const struct nvkm_event_func
155nv50_disp_chan_uevent = {
156 .ctor = nv50_disp_chan_uevent_ctor,
157 .init = nv50_disp_chan_uevent_init,
158 .fini = nv50_disp_chan_uevent_fini,
159};
160
161static int
162nv50_disp_chan_rd32(struct nvkm_object *object, u64 addr, u32 *data)
163{
164 struct nv50_disp_chan *chan = nv50_disp_chan(object);
165 struct nv50_disp *disp = chan->root->disp;
166 struct nvkm_device *device = disp->base.engine.subdev.device;
167 *data = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x640000 + (chan->chid * 0x1000) + addr);
168 return 0;
169}
170
171static int
172nv50_disp_chan_wr32(struct nvkm_object *object, u64 addr, u32 data)
173{
174 struct nv50_disp_chan *chan = nv50_disp_chan(object);
175 struct nv50_disp *disp = chan->root->disp;
176 struct nvkm_device *device = disp->base.engine.subdev.device;
177 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x640000 + (chan->chid * 0x1000) + addr, data);
178 return 0;
179}
180
181static int
182nv50_disp_chan_ntfy(struct nvkm_object *object, u32 type,
183 struct nvkm_event **pevent)
184{
185 struct nv50_disp_chan *chan = nv50_disp_chan(object);
186 struct nv50_disp *disp = chan->root->disp;
187 switch (type) {
188 case NV50_DISP_CORE_CHANNEL_DMA_V0_NTFY_UEVENT:
189 *pevent = &disp->uevent;
190 return 0;
191 default:
192 break;
193 }
194 return -EINVAL;
195}
196
197static int
198#ifdef __NetBSD__
199nv50_disp_chan_map(struct nvkm_object *object, bus_space_tag_t *tagp,
200 u64 *addr, u32 *size)
201#else
202nv50_disp_chan_map(struct nvkm_object *object, u64 *addr, u32 *size)
203#endif
204{
205 struct nv50_disp_chan *chan = nv50_disp_chan(object);
206 struct nv50_disp *disp = chan->root->disp;
207 struct nvkm_device *device = disp->base.engine.subdev.device;
208#ifdef __NetBSD__
209 *tagp = device->func->resource_tag(device, 0);
210#endif
211 *addr = device->func->resource_addr(device, 0) +
212 0x640000 + (chan->chid * 0x1000);
213 *size = 0x001000;
214 return 0;
215}
216
217static int
218nv50_disp_chan_child_new(const struct nvkm_oclass *oclass,
219 void *data, u32 size, struct nvkm_object **pobject)
220{
221 struct nv50_disp_chan *chan = nv50_disp_chan(oclass->parent);
222 return chan->func->child_new(chan, oclass, data, size, pobject);
223}
224
225static int
226nv50_disp_chan_child_get(struct nvkm_object *object, int index,
227 struct nvkm_oclass *oclass)
228{
229 struct nv50_disp_chan *chan = nv50_disp_chan(object);
230 if (chan->func->child_get) {
231 int ret = chan->func->child_get(chan, index, oclass);
232 if (ret == 0)
233 oclass->ctor = nv50_disp_chan_child_new;
234 return ret;
235 }
236 return -EINVAL;
237}
238
239static int
240nv50_disp_chan_fini(struct nvkm_object *object, bool suspend)
241{
242 struct nv50_disp_chan *chan = nv50_disp_chan(object);
243 chan->func->fini(chan);
244 return 0;
245}
246
247static int
248nv50_disp_chan_init(struct nvkm_object *object)
249{
250 struct nv50_disp_chan *chan = nv50_disp_chan(object);
251 return chan->func->init(chan);
252}
253
254static void *
255nv50_disp_chan_dtor(struct nvkm_object *object)
256{
257 struct nv50_disp_chan *chan = nv50_disp_chan(object);
258 struct nv50_disp *disp = chan->root->disp;
259 if (chan->chid >= 0)
260 disp->chan[chan->chid] = NULL;
261 return chan->func->dtor ? chan->func->dtor(chan) : chan;
262}
263
264static const struct nvkm_object_func
265nv50_disp_chan = {
266 .dtor = nv50_disp_chan_dtor,
267 .init = nv50_disp_chan_init,
268 .fini = nv50_disp_chan_fini,
269 .rd32 = nv50_disp_chan_rd32,
270 .wr32 = nv50_disp_chan_wr32,
271 .ntfy = nv50_disp_chan_ntfy,
272 .map = nv50_disp_chan_map,
273 .sclass = nv50_disp_chan_child_get,
274};
275
276int
277nv50_disp_chan_ctor(const struct nv50_disp_chan_func *func,
278 const struct nv50_disp_chan_mthd *mthd,
279 struct nv50_disp_root *root, int chid, int head,
280 const struct nvkm_oclass *oclass,
281 struct nv50_disp_chan *chan)
282{
283 struct nv50_disp *disp = root->disp;
284
285 nvkm_object_ctor(&nv50_disp_chan, oclass, &chan->object);
286 chan->func = func;
287 chan->mthd = mthd;
288 chan->root = root;
289 chan->chid = chid;
290 chan->head = head;
291
292 if (disp->chan[chan->chid]) {
293 chan->chid = -1;
294 return -EBUSY;
295 }
296 disp->chan[chan->chid] = chan;
297 return 0;
298}
299
300int
301nv50_disp_chan_new_(const struct nv50_disp_chan_func *func,
302 const struct nv50_disp_chan_mthd *mthd,
303 struct nv50_disp_root *root, int chid, int head,
304 const struct nvkm_oclass *oclass,
305 struct nvkm_object **pobject)
306{
307 struct nv50_disp_chan *chan;
308
309 if (!(chan = kzalloc(sizeof(*chan), GFP_KERNEL)))
310 return -ENOMEM;
311 *pobject = &chan->object;
312
313 return nv50_disp_chan_ctor(func, mthd, root, chid, head, oclass, chan);
314}
